On Tue, 31 Jul 2001, Kyle wrote:

> You don't need to Heli-coil it. Run a bolt from the inside of the case down.

<procedure snipped>

Kyle, what is the thread length of the bolts you use?  They have to be
just long enough to poke out of the sump plate, but not so long as to
bottom out in the blind-end nuts.  If you use regular nuts here they will
drip oil, so the correct length is important.

George Lyle

